### Configure Transformers.js to Use Local Models in Node.js

Source: https://github.com/huggingface/transformers.js/blob/main/docs/source/tutorials/node.md

This JavaScript code demonstrates how to configure Transformers.js to use locally stored model files. By setting `env.localModelPath`, you can point the library to a directory containing your models, and by setting `env.allowRemoteModels` to `false`, you can disable loading models from the Hugging Face Hub.

```javascript
env.localModelPath = '/path/to/models/';
env.allowRemoteModels = false;

```

