### Run Florence-2 with per-module dtypes on WebGPU

Source: https://github.com/huggingface/transformers.js/blob/main/docs/source/guides/dtypes.md

This snippet shows how to load the Florence-2 model with specific data types for different modules (e.g., `embed_tokens`, `vision_encoder`, `encoder_model`) using a dtype mapping and the `webgpu` device. This allows for fine-grained control over quantization for complex models.

```javascript
import { Florence2ForConditionalGeneration } from "@huggingface/transformers";

const model = await Florence2ForConditionalGeneration.from_pretrained(
  "onnx-community/Florence-2-base-ft",
  {
    dtype: {
      embed_tokens: "fp16",
      vision_encoder: "fp16",
      encoder_model: "q4",
      decoder_model_merged: "q4",
    },
    device: "webgpu",
  },
);
```

