### Customize Transformers.js Environment Settings

Source: https://github.com/huggingface/transformers.js/blob/main/README.md

Demonstrates how to configure environment variables for Transformers.js to control model paths, remote model access, and WASM binary locations. This is useful for self-hosting models or optimizing resource loading.

```javascript
import { env } from '@huggingface/transformers';

// Specify a custom location for models (defaults to '/models/').
env.localModelPath = '/path/to/models/';

// Disable the loading of remote models from the Hugging Face Hub:
env.allowRemoteModels = false;

// Set location of .wasm files. Defaults to use a CDN.
env.backends.onnx.wasm.wasmPaths = '/path/to/files/';

```

