### Initialize Object Detection Pipeline (JavaScript)

Source: https://github.com/huggingface/transformers.js/blob/main/docs/source/tutorials/vanilla-js.md

Creates an object detection pipeline using the `pipeline()` function from Transformers.js. It takes the task name ('object-detection') and the model identifier ('Xenova/detr-resnet-50') as arguments. This function is asynchronous and may take time to download the model.

```javascript
const detector = await pipeline("object-detection", "Xenova/detr-resnet-50");
