### Transformers.js Pipeline API - Basic Sentiment Analysis

Source: https://context7.com/huggingface/transformers.js/llms.txt

Demonstrates the basic usage of the `pipeline` function for sentiment analysis. It automatically downloads the default model on the first run and processes both single and multiple text inputs for batch analysis.

```javascript
import { pipeline } from '@huggingface/transformers';

// Create a sentiment analysis pipeline (downloads model on first run)
const classifier = await pipeline('sentiment-analysis');

// Single input
const result = await classifier('I love transformers!');
console.log(result);
// Output: [{'label': 'POSITIVE', 'score': 0.999817686}]

// Multiple inputs (batch processing)
const results = await classifier([
    'I love transformers!',
    'I hate bugs in my code!',
    'The weather is neutral today.'
]);
console.log(results);
// Output: [
//   {'label': 'POSITIVE', 'score': 0.9998},
//   {'label': 'NEGATIVE', 'score': 0.9982},
//   {'label': 'NEUTRAL', 'score': 0.8745}
// ]
```

